@maisonmargielafragrances Sailing Day has been on my wishlist for a while, and it doesn’t disappoint. It captures a fresh, natural aquatic essence that feels subtle and effortless. 🌊

What I love most is how beautifully Sailing Day pairs with vanilla and citrus-based fragrances. The vanilla adds a soft, creamy warmth that contrasts the crisp, aquatic notes in such an elegant way, making the scent feel more rounded and cozy. On the other hand, layering it with citrus notes enhances the clean, fresh aspects of Sailing Day, amplifying its breezy, oceanic character.

It’s the kind of fragrance that works seamlessly for daytime wear, especially in warmer seasons when you want something light, clean, and invigorating.

Notes Breakdown (source: Fragrantica):
Top: Sea Notes, Aldehydes, Coriander, Red Pepper
Middle: Juniper, Iris, Amyl Salicylate, Rose
Base: Seaweed, Ambergris, Cedar, Amberwood

It’s perfect for anyone who loves aquatic scents and wants something versatile for layering to create their own signature touch.

@yslbeauty Make Me Blush Liquid Blush
Shade: 44 Nude Lavallière

I’ve been reaching for this liquid blush in 44 Nude Lavallière, and I’m obsessed! It’s a soft, dusty rose that looks so natural and effortless on my skin tone—perfect for that “barely-there” flush of color. I find that two tiny dots give me just the right amount of pigment to show up beautifully without looking overdone.

The formula blends like a dream and melts into the skin for a seamless, second-skin finish. It doesn’t sit on top of my makeup or disrupt any powders, which is a huge win for me. Plus, it’s not overly bright or overpowering, so it’s perfect for everyday wear or those minimal “no-makeup” makeup days.

This was my first pick from the range, and now I can’t stop thinking about trying more shades—blush addiction incoming!

Have you tried the Make Me Blush line yet? If so, which shades are you loving? I’d love to hear your favorites!

#AD | @mywishcare ceramide lip balms! ✨

If you’re someone who struggles with lip pigmentation, look no further—here’s your ultimate solution!

This lip balm offers the perfect balance of nourishment and just the right amount of tint to suit your needs. Whether you prefer a clear finish or a pop of color, there’s something for everyone—take your pick!

Formulated with powerhouse ingredients like niacinamide, kojic acid, and ceramides, this balm works to lighten dark pigmentation, repair damaged skin, and provide deep hydration, leaving your lips soft, smooth, and visibly healthier.

What’s more, it contains SPF PA+++, which shields your delicate lips from harmful UV rays, preventing further darkening and sun damage.

Say goodbye to pigmented lips and hello to a nourished, even-toned pout—your perfect everyday lip companion!

@rhode Peptide Lip Tint in Cinnamon Roll 🤎✨

This was definitely an impulse buy for me, but I have no regrets!

I’m usually not one for shimmery lip products, but this one is such a stunner—especially paired with a neutral brown lip liner. It’s heavenly. The subtle shimmer gives the perfect touch without overpowering or drawing too much attention, and the sheer brown gloss just melts onto the lips beautifully.

Oh, and the scent? It smells exactly like a cinnamon roll—absolutely obsessed! 🥰

If you love sheer, brown-toned glosses, this is such a great pick.

@nudestix matte + glow core blush in the shade pink ice 🧊🎀

I absolutely adore this formula! This is actually my second blush from the range, and I find myself reaching for it constantly. Pink Ice delivers the most beautiful, subtle flush of soft pink that feels so natural and flattering on the skin, while the core’s glow adds the perfect touch of radiance. It strikes that ideal balance of matte and luminous, giving you a healthy, winter-perfect sheen without emphasizing texture.

It melts into the skin seamlessly, never looking patchy or overdone. For those cooler winter months, it’s been my go-to for a fresh, “just-in-from-the-cold” vibe.

Have you tried this range yet? If so, what’s your favorite shade? I’d love to know!
